EITS: Ability to borrow a high performance laptop for teaching both online and in person. I borrowed a laptop from the IT helpdesk that barely works. I also received very poor, unkind treatment from one of the helpdesk managers at the Institute.

COMMENT: It is very frustrating to see that there is not a category for ICC and Language Studies in the primary academic division section above. This has happened many times before with other surveys.

EITS: A complete orientation to relevant technology.

ELS: A more streamlined approach to accessing scholarly publication pdfs would help a lot. Often I find a reference as I am researching and have to search in many parts of the library to determine if we can access a pdf.

full text, PDF access to more journals relevant to my field would be helpful.
